  "section_name": "Financial Analysis",
  "text": "Airbnb demonstrated strong revenue recovery in Q2 2025, with revenue reaching $3,096,000,000, representing 36.27% year-over-year growth compared to Q2 2024 revenue of $2,748,000,000 (C002, C023, K001). This rebound follows a challenging Q1 2025 period where revenue declined 39.12% YoY to $2,272,000,000, indicating significant seasonality in the travel business (C009, K001). Profitability metrics showed meaningful improvement in Q2 2025, with operating margin expanding to 19.77% and net margin reaching 20.74%, compared to Q1 2025's compressed margins of 1.67% operating and 6.78% net (C004, C006, C011, C013). Year-over-year, Q2 2025 operating margin improved from 18.09% in Q2 2024, while net margin remained relatively stable at 20.20% in the prior year period (C025, C027). However, profitability remains below the peak levels observed in Q3 2024, when operating and net margins reached 40.86% and 36.66% respectively, reflecting the typical summer travel season strength (C018, C020).",
